<title>USA: Sabratek, Coram in purchase deal.</title>
<headline>Sabratek, Coram in purchase deal.</headline>
<dateline>NILES, Ill. 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sabratek Corp and Coram Healthcare Corp said Monday they reached a definitive agreement under which Coram will buy Sabratek's seamless multi-therapy infusion pumps and related telemedicine technology.</p>
<p>Financial terms of the agreement were not disclosed, but the companies said Coram's initial order has been placed.</p>
<p>Coram, based in Denver, provides home patient care. Sabratek provides equipment for the alternative-site healthcare market.</p>
<p>((--Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
